(1, 'en_US', 'descriptionShort', '<p>Dear Colleagues,</p><p>Â </p><p>Faculty of Psychology Universitas Indonesia is currently commissioning a new international journal: <strong>Psychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)</strong>. We would like to invite researchers to publish their research results in our journal in the form of original research papers or case study and review papers related to issues on human behavior in the urban context, such as:</p><ul><li>Urban mental health and well-being</li><li>Education and child development in urban society</li><li>Intergroup relation, acculturation, and identity formation in urban contexts</li><li>Urban social issues (ex: poverty, traffic, crime and violence)</li><li>Urban culture</li><li>Urban issues on employment and organizational behavior</li></ul><p>Â </p><p>The intended audience for this journal is scholars and practitioners interested in urban issues.</p><p>Â </p><p>This journal will be published twice a year: June and December. The first publication is intended to be published in December 2017. Therefore, the submissions will be opened until the end of October 2017. See authorâ€™s guideline attached.</p><p>Â </p><p>We are highly appreciated if you can let us know before you send your manuscripts. Thank you for your participation.</p><p>Â </p><p>Â </p><p>Editor-In-Chief,</p><p>Prof. Sri Hartati R-Suradijono, MA., Ph.D</p>', 'string'),
(1, 'en_US', 'description', '', 'string'),
(2, 'en_US', 'title', 'Published Articles: PRoUSt Volume 1 Number 1 April 2018', 'string'),
(2, 'en_US', 'descriptionShort', '<p>We are pleased to announce that Psychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt) has published the first volume and number in April 2018. Electronic version available online <a id="tinymce" class="mceContentBody" dir="ltr" href="/index.php/journal/issue/view/2" data-gramm_id="4b76aef7-c21c-bb47-8f32-8acfe1e61b5d" data-gramm="true" data-gramm_editor="true">here</a>.</p><p><img src="/public/site/images/proust/REV_4_mini1.png" alt="" width="248" height="352" /></p>', 'string'),
