(4, 2, 256, 10, 10, 22, '[PRoUSt] Editor Decision on your manuscript', 'Dear Dr. Sonn,\r\n\r\nThank you for considering the Psychological Research on Urban Society as an outlet for your work entitled "Creative and arts based methodologies:\r\nExpanding applied psychologiesâ€™ resources for intervention and\r\nempowerment".  I have now received two expert reviews of your manuscript, and I have also read the manuscript independently of the reviewer comments. Both reviewers and I agree that the topic is important and applicable in urban context on how to embrace the marginalized indigenous people into the urban context. However, we all are in agreement that the manuscript still needs to be revised to fit our theme in the journal, which in my opinion can be easily done by providing urban context in the introduction section. I also include reviewersâ€™ comments on the manuscript for your consideration.\r\n\r\nTo submit a revision, please login with your account http://proust.ui.ac.id with your username and password. If you have any problem regarding this step, please email us at proust@ui.ac.id . To see the results and submit the revision, click your manuscriptâ€™s title then Review tab. The upload box is in the bottom of the page.\r\n\r\nAs your manuscript needs a minor revision, I would like to receive the revision within 10 days from the receipt of this letter. Please let me know if you would like to have additional time.\r\n\r\nYours sincerely,\r\n\r\nDebora Eflina Purba\r\nEditor\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society\r\n\r\n\r\nReviewers'' comments:\r\n\r\nReviewer #1\r\nThis paper contains an explanation of the approaches and methods that are new to psychology. The topic raised is not common to psychology in general. In some parts, the writing is very dense with a reference that is also quite new, in a sense not yet widely known by the community of psychology in general.\r\nThere needs to be an explanation that makes it easier for audiences from diverse backgrounds to understand what this article is saying.\r\nIn the introduction it is necessary to sit down the issues that will be discussed more clearly. It may also need an explanation of critical psychology and liberation psychology so that the audience can follow the course of reasoning in this article.\r\nConsider the communicative aspects of this paper as mentioned in the description on the Proust web site: "Authors of theoretical or highly empirical papers are encouraged to communicate the practical implications of their studies, and authors of practice-oriented papers should clearly elaborate the theoretical approach they are using." \r\nAdjustment style is important to do considering the substance of this paper is important to be known by the psychology community, including practitioners.\r\n\r\nReviewer #2\r\nPlease explain why the topic is relevant to be published under PROUST, as PROUST is specifically about research on urban society - ex. are there lessons from the methods to gain knowledge about urban society.\r\n\r\n\r\nDebora Eflina Purba\r\nEditor\r\neflina@ui.ac.id\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/', '2018-02-21 15:22:22', NULL, 1),
(5, 2, 256, 10, 10, 22, '[PRoUSt] Editor Decision', 'Christopher Sonn:\r\n\r\nWe have reached a decision regarding your submission to Psychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt), "Creative and arts based methodologies: Expanding applied psychologiesâ€™ resources for intervention and empowerment".\r\n\r\nOur decision is: Revisions Required\r\n\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society\r\nproust@ui.ac.id\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/', '2018-02-22 11:35:29', NULL, 1),
(6, 2, 256, 10, 10, 22, '[PRoUSt] Editor Decision', 'Christopher Sonn:\r\n\r\nWe have reached a decision regarding your submission to Psychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt), "Creative and arts based methodologies: Expanding applied psychologiesâ€™ resources for intervention and empowerment".\r\n\r\nOur decision is: Revisions Required\r\n\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society\r\nproust@ui.ac.id\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/', '2018-02-22 16:28:02', NULL, 1),
(7, 2, 256, 17, 17, 32, '[PRoUSt] Editor Decision on your manuscript', 'Dear Mita Puspita Sary,\r\n\r\nThank you for considering the Psychological Research on Urban Society as an outlet for your work.  I have received an expert review of your manuscript entitled " Prevalence of Mental Health Problems among Adolescents in DKI Jakarta", and I have also read the manuscript independently of the reviewerâ€™s comments. Both the reviewer and I agree that the topic is important and is in line with our journalâ€™s theme. However, we also are in agreement that the manuscript still needs to be revised to meet the standard of scientific article. Below I include the excellent and detailed comments from our reviewer for your consideration to improve the manuscript.\r\n\r\nTo submit a revision, please login with your account http://proust.ui.ac.id with your username and password. If you have any problem regarding this step, please email us at proust@ui.ac.id . To see the results and submit the revision, click your manuscriptâ€™s title then Review tab. The upload box is in the bottom of the page.\r\n\r\nI would like to receive the revision within 14 days from the receipt of this letter. Please let me know if you would like to have additional time.\r\n\r\nYours sincerely,\r\n\r\nProf. Sri Hartati R. Suradijono, M.A., Ph.D \r\nEditor-in-Chief\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society\r\n\r\nReviewerâ€™s comments:\r\nThis manuscript describes an effort to investigate prevalence of mental health problems among adolescents in the capital of Indonesia, Jakarta.  The authors found that the adolescents have quite a high number of different mental health problems. This should be an alarm for the mental health practitioners and the government.  The research questions is important considering the increase awareness of mental health problems in Indonesia. However, the design of the study and how it is reported is not in the acceptable level to be published in a scientific journal.\r\nMajor comments:\r\n1. The area of mental health problems was not defined clearly in the introduction and the method section. I assume that (i) conduct-related problems or disorders (ii) anxiety), (iii) mood, depression and suicide-related were the scope of the mental health investigated in this study (Par 4 of Introduction). However, it was not clarified in the Method: e.g. the definition and scope of each area and which instrument(s) to measure the corresponding area of problem. \r\n2. No detailed explanation of sampling procedure. How to choose one senior high school from each area: randomized by computer, flip a coin, etc? Does one senior high school per area of Jakarta enough to represent numerous high school in the area (which also not clearly stated in the manuscript)? What procedure implemented to select which grade, class, student to be interviewed? \r\n3. Majority of the measures used were not properly adapted to Indonesian culture following a standardized translation protocol that followed international recommendations. No reference of such procedure stated in the manuscript. For instance, the authors stated that â€œwe used PLEs instrument that has been translated and adapted into Indonesian language by the Community Mental Health Research Group, Faculty of Psychology Universitas Indonesia in 2015â€ but not refer it to any publication that can be recheck by others. Another example is for HSCL-25, â€œThe cutoff score 1.75 was used to divide category of participants into high and low depression/anxietyâ€ without any reference how this cut-off obtained. Any results produced by these instruments might be interpreted cautiously. \r\n4. The results could be (partly) explained by socio-demographic variables. However, the information concerning this data is really limited. It would be useful to explore more in-depth. \r\n5. It is clearly observed that the authors did not use any reference management software such as Mendeley or EndNote. Therefore the citations and reference list needed major improvements.  \r\n6. The first paragraph of Discussion section usually serves as summary of the aim(s) of the study and main findings. Please revise.\r\nMinor comments:\r\nAbstract\r\n1.	â€˜786â€™ should be added in the sentence of â€œA total ofâ€¦.adolescentsâ€ \r\n2.	Please write all the questionnaires used in this study\r\n3.	The words â€œnumerous mental health problemsâ€ are not clear enough. Please describe the results.\r\n\r\nIntroduction\r\n4.	Please provide reference to the Riskesdas 2013\r\n5.	Please follow the APA reference style for the whole manuscript\r\n\r\nMethod\r\n6.	Move the sentences â€œA total of 786 high school students aged between 15-18 years old participated in this study. The number of female participants were 51%, and the male participants were 49%â€ to result section.\r\n7.	Please describe what was the form of the demographic questions: e.g. paper-and-pencil questionnaire, oral questions, etc\r\n8.	Move the sentence â€œAll of the demographic information is presented in table 1â€ to Result section\r\n9.	Please provide the reference of cultural adaptation of each measurement tool in this study.\r\n10.	Please mention the six types of health-risk behavior measured by the Youth Risk Behavior Survey.\r\n\r\nResults\r\n11.	Please order the results according to the order of measures in the Method section. This will help the readers. \r\n12.	Please always mention in which table the result can be seen. For instance, the prevalence of loneliness results only mentioned that 57.4% of participants experienced loneliness but not mentioning that this can be seen in Table 2.\r\n\r\nDiscussions\r\n13.	The authors mentioned that â€œMany of the participants also experienced loneliness, internalizing problems and externalizing problemsâ€ and listed similar results from other investigations. It will be clearer for the readers if the similarities and differences between this study and the similar ones described in more details.\r\n14.	â€œSome of these emotional and conduct problems would also be evident from the substance use conditions in this study population, which were also highâ€. Any correlation analysis conducted to support this statement?\r\n15.	Itâ€™s better not to write â€œThis study has many limitationsâ€. One could use â€œSome limitations of the present study should be considered.â€\r\n16.	The authors mentioned the application of non-proportioned cluster sampling in selecting the samples as a strong point. However, no previous explanation of this sampling technique in the Method section, only about multistage random sampling. Please explain more.\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/', '2018-02-23 13:55:09', NULL, 1),
(8, 2, 256, 11, 11, 10, '[PRoUSt]', 'Dear Dr. Henry Otgaar,\r\n\r\nThank you for submitting your manuscript to PRoUSt. After careful consideration, we feel that it has merit, but is not suitable for publication as it currently stands. Therefore, my decision is "Revisions required".  \r\n\r\nBased on the comments and evaluation of the reviewer, we invite you to submit a revised version of the manuscript that addresses the points made by the reviewer.  A Word file of the reviewed manuscript has been uploaded and attached to this e-mail.  Please use the file to start your revision.  Finally, we encourage you to submit your revision to PRoUSt within 14 days of the date of this decision.\r\n\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\n\r\nDr. Agnes Sianipar\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/', '2018-02-23 21:14:42', NULL, 1),
(9, 2, 256, 16, 16, 29, '[PRoUSt] Editor Decision on your manuscript', 'Dear Prof. Cecilia Cheng,\r\n\r\nThank you for considering the Psychological Research on Urban Society as an outlet for your work.  I have received an expert review of your manuscript entitled "A Two-Dimensional Framework for Analyzing Facebook Use and Subjective Well-Being", and I have also read the manuscript independently of the reviewerâ€™s comments. Both the reviewer and I agree that the topic is important and is in line with our journalâ€™s theme. However, we also are in agreement that the manuscript still needs to be revised to meet the standard of scientific article. Below I include the excellent and detailed comments from our reviewer for your consideration to improve the manuscript.\r\n\r\nTo submit a revision, please login with your account http://proust.ui.ac.id\r\nwith your username and password. If you have any problem regarding this\r\nstep, please email us at proust@ui.ac.id.\r\n\r\nI would like to receive the revision within 14 days from the receipt of this\r\nletter. Please let me know if you would like to have additional time to revise the paper.\r\n\r\nYours sincerely,\r\n\r\nProf. Sri Hartati R. Suradijono, M.A., Ph.D\r\nEditor-in-Chief\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society\r\n\r\nReviewerâ€™s comments:\r\n\r\nThis manuscript is well-written, and would be a good topic for this journal. However, the author needs to pay attention to some things to improve the paper:\r\n\r\n1. This paper needs a general introduction part that brings the audience clarity on the research questions and hypotheses. Perhaps authors need to explain more about previous research gap and the theoretical contributions from this study. Please also add the context of urban setting in the introduction.\r\n2. Figure 1 in the introduction is missing. Please add.\r\n3. In the method section- Participants, please add information on the SD of age. Another demographic characteristic of the participants, such as frequency of Facebook use, will be beneficial to add in this section. \r\n4. In the method section- Measures. The explanation about Facebook use and satisfaction were not detailed. Please explain more about the three subscales, the two sections, sample of items, and who developed the scale. For every measure in this study, please add the explanation about sample of items and the reliability of each measure. \r\n5. One of the objectives of this study was to develop and validate a new measure for assessing Facebook use and satisfaction. However there was no explanation about the validation testing of the new measure in the result section. In the first part of the result, please explain about the reliability and validity of the scale. \r\n6. The results and discussion section are combined. It is better to separate them and discuss thoroughly about the results. \r\n7. The conclusion section is missing.\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/', '2018-02-27 17:58:35', NULL, 1),
(19, 2, 256, 16, 16, 29, '[PRoUSt] Editor Decision', 'Prof. Cecilia Cheng:\r\n\r\nWe have reached a decision regarding your submission to Psychological Research on Urban Society, "A Two-Dimensional Framework for Analyzing Facebook Use and Subjective Well-Being".\r\n\r\nOur decision is: Revisions Required\r\n\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society\r\nproust@ui.ac.id\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/', '2018-03-23 11:42:37', NULL, 1),
(11, 2, 256, 15, 15, 10, '[PRoUSt] Editorial Letter on your manuscript', 'Consequences of False Memories in Eyewitness Testimony: \r\nA Review and Implications for Chinese Legal Practice\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society\r\n\r\nDear Jianqin Wang,\r\n\r\nI''m pleased to inform you that your paper titled "Consequences of False Memories in Eyewitness Testimony: A Review and Implications for Chinese Legal Practice" has been accepted for publication in the Psychological Research on Urban Society. You will be notified later once the proof-reading process on your manuscript is finished.\r\n\r\nIt was accepted on 03/01/2018.\r\n\r\nI would like to thank you for considering the Psychological Research on Urban Society for an outlet for your work.\r\n\r\nWith kind regards,\r\n\r\nSri Hartati R-Suradijono\r\nEditor-in-Chief\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/', '2018-03-01 17:42:51', NULL, 1),
(12, 2, 256, 8, 8, 11, '[PRoUSt] Editorial Letter on your manuscript', 'Dear Dr. Elizabeth Kristi Poerwandari,\r\n\r\nI''m pleased to inform you that your paper titled "Premarital Sexual Compliance among Urban Indonesian Women: A Descriptive Study" has been accepted for publication in the Psychological\r\nResearch on Urban Society. Your paper will be sent to proof-reading process, and you will be notified later when it is finished.\r\n\r\nIt was accepted on 05/03/2018.\r\n\r\nI would like to thank you for considering the Psychological Research on\r\nUrban Society for an outlet for your work.\r\n\r\nWith kind regards,\r\n\r\nDebora Eflina Purba\r\nEditor\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/', '2018-03-06 10:28:17', NULL, 1),
(13, 2, 256, 21, 21, 27, '[PRoUSt] Editorial letter on your manuscript', 'Dear Dr. E. S. Jaya,\r\n\r\nThank you for considering the Psychological Research on Urban Society as an outlet for your work.  I have now received an expert review of your manuscript entitled "Psychotic Experiences, Depressive Symptoms, Anxiety Symptoms and Common Mental Health Risk Factors of Urban and Non-Urban Dwellers in Indonesia," and I have also read the manuscript independently of the reviewer comments. Both the reviewer and I agree that the topic is important and fit-in well with our journal theme. However, I agree with the reviewer that the manuscript still needs to be revised to improve its readability, which in my opinion can be easily done by making clear concept definitions that you use in your manuscript and making small corrections as suggested by the reviewer. I include reviewersâ€™ comments on the manuscript for your consideration. \r\n\r\nRegarding suggestion no. 5 from the reviewer, if it is not possible for you to rerun the test by controlling demographic variables, I suggest that you mention this in the future direction of the study. Having said this, I also suggest that you soften your tone in your conclusion of the difference between urban and rural dwellers. Please be sure to include a point-by-point response to each of the issues raised by the reviewer.\r\n\r\nTo submit a revision, please login with your account http://proust.ui.ac.id with your username and password. If you have any problem regarding this step, please email us at proust@ui.ac.id.\r\n\r\nAs your manuscript needs a minor revision, I would like to receive the revision within ten days from the receipt of this letter. Please let me know if you would like to have additional time.\r\n\r\nYours sincerely,\r\n\r\nDebora Eflina Purba\r\nEditor\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society\r\n\r\nReviewers'' comments:\r\n\r\nThis manuscript explores the prevalence of common risk factors and symptoms of mental health between the urban and non-urban inhabitants in Indonesia. The authors found that respondents living in the urban area had higher scores in the risk factors: loneliness, bullying at home, and negative schema, and mental disorder symptoms: positive symptom and depression. Therefore, they conclude that living in urban might linked to higher exposure to mental health risk factor and more possible to have mental health problems. This manuscript is well-written but, in my opinion, incomplete. See below for some comments and questions:   \r\n1)	Please provide page number to help the reviewers address specific comment/issue in the manuscript\r\n2)	2.1. Participants and procedure: The definition of urban and non-urban in this study was not clearly defined. In the limitation section of discussion, the author mentioned about â€œin this study, urbanicity was conceptualized as the current place of residence.â€ How was the current place of residence judged as urban or non-urban: government administration definition, respondent self-judged, etc?  \r\n3)	Results â€“ Participant characteristics: Itâ€™s better to provide a table of demographic characteristics of the participants. This will help the readers to understand easier the sample and level of representativeness. How many of this study sample was urban and non-urban? Some of the sentences in this part are not clear enough, for example: (i) Participants were significantly different in terms of age (t(680.460) = -4.11, p < .01), income (t(830) = -2.49, p < .05), education (U = 96,316.500, p < .01), and SES (U = 93,813.00, p < .05).. which participants was refereed in this result? (ii) which measures were being referred to â€œâ€¦ with non-urban participants showing higher mean scores across measures than urban participantsâ€? \r\n4)	4.1. Main findings: â€œParticipants living in the non-urban area were significantly older, had a higher level of income, education, as well as socio-economic status.â€ I find this as strange and unlikely! Could you elaborate more on this? \r\n5)	3.2. Urban and non-urban differences: t-tests or Mann-Whitney U test was applied comparing each variable between the two groups. Would it better if this comparison is also controlling for sociodemographic factors; i.e., gender, education, SES since the two samples were significantly different regarding sociodemographic factors? Furthermore, the authors have the risk factors, groups (urban vs. non-urban), and the symptoms of mental disorders: why not model them and see whether the place of residence plays a significant role? \r\n6)	3.2. Urban and non-urban differences: The significant differences between urban and non-urban found in this study should be seen in the light of the statistical power of almost 1000 respondents. As can be seen, all the significant differences effect sizes were small: 0.14-0.25. This should be mentioned in the result and discussion section. \r\n7)	Limitation: The possibility of access to the internet, hence to enroll n this study, is higher in an urban area than rural. Would this be considered as a possible bias? \r\n8)	Conclusion: In my opinion, the conclusion of â€œliving in an urban environment is one risk factor contributing to a poorer mental health conditionâ€ is too strong considering the simple descriptive analysis as conducted in the present manuscript.\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/', '2018-03-07 08:49:47', NULL, 1),
(14, 2, 65536, 10, 10, 22, 'Creative and arts based methodologies: Expanding applied psychologiesâ€™ resources for intervention and empowerment', 'Dear Editor\r\n\r\nWe are very grateful for the reviewers report on our article "Creative and arts based methodologies: Expanding psychologies'' resources for intervention and empowerment".   The feedback is very valuable and we agree that the focus does not explicitly align with the theme of the journal.  There are reasons; mainly the paper focusses on methodologies and builds on a presentation to a conference held at UI in 2017.  We submitted it to PROUST following an invitation from conference organisers.\r\n\r\nWe have now considered the feedback, and have decided that the paper cannot easily be reworked to fit the theme of the journal without compromising the original aim.  Therefore, we have regrettably decided to withdraw the paper from consideration for publication in PROUST.  We hope to submit some work in the future that is more suited to the theme of the journal.\r\n\r\n\r\nRegards\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/', '2018-03-17 23:09:17', NULL, 1),
