(33, 2, 256, 34, 34, 58, '[PRoUSt] Editor Decision', 'Galih Kartika:\r\n\r\nWe have reached a decision regarding your submission to Psychological Research on Urban Society, "JOB SATISFACTION AND TURNOVER INTENTION : THE MEDIATING EFFECT OF AFFECTIVE COMMITMENT".\r\n\r\nOur decision is: Revisions Required\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nHamdi Muluk\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society\r\nhamdim@ui.ac.id\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/', '2018-07-11 08:37:42', NULL, 1),
(34, 2, 256, 34, 34, 58, '[PRoUSt] Editor Decision', 'Galih Kartika:\r\n\r\nWe have reached a decision regarding your submission to Psychological Research on Urban Society, "JOB SATISFACTION AND TURNOVER INTENTION : THE MEDIATING EFFECT OF AFFECTIVE COMMITMENT".\r\n\r\nOur decision is: Revisions Required. Please address issues raised by the reviewer below.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nHamdi Muluk\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society\r\nhamdim@ui.ac.id\r\n\r\nReviewer 1:\r\nThis manuscript investigates the mediating effect of affective commitment on the relationship between job satisfaction and turnover intention in international school teachers, which is then supported by data. The writing of this manuscript needs to be improved to help future readers comprehend it. See below for some comments and questions:   \r\n1)	Please provide page number to help the reviewers address specific comment/issue in the manuscript\r\n2)	Please check the English with a native or English service, or at least with Grammarly app. Some articles such as â€˜aâ€™ or â€˜theâ€™ are missing from the text. \r\n3)	Please check thoroughly any typo: e.g., â€˜organizatiomâ€™ in the third paragraph of the Introduction section\r\n4)	Participants and procedure:  the second paragraph should be in the Results section and presented in Table 1 since this is the result, not a method. Part of Table 1 that presented the correlation between study variables should be in Table 2. Table 2 in the original manuscript should be Table 3.\r\n5)	Participants and procedure: please write the long form of HR when first mentioned.\r\n6)	Participants and procedure, third paragraph: how did the authors â€œcontrolled for educational level and tenureâ€. Is it in data collection process: i.e., exclude those with lower educational level or in statistical analysis: i.e., include the two variables in regression analysis? If the former, please describe it in the paragraph. If the latter, please describe it in the Statistical Analysis sub-section.\r\n7)	Measures: please add whether higher scores mean higher turnover/job satisfaction/affective commitment in each of the instruments.\r\n8)	Statistical analysis: please add a description of correlation analysis implemented between variables as being shown in Table 1. Since some variables are dummy coded and some are not, therefore the analysis being used should be different. Please specify this in the statistical analysis section.\r\n9)	Table 1: Mean of Gender (1,64) and educational level (3,57) do not make sense. Its better to write percentage of males in Gender and bachelor in educational level to help readers. \r\n10)	Table 1: (i) revise the use of comma as decimal place and use period instead, because this journal uses English language (ii) add 0 in the fraction numbers: e.g., 0.230 instead of .230 (iii) be consistent in the amount of digit for decimal, some are 2 digits for decimal, some are 3.\r\n11)	Table 3: the author wrote â€˜aâ€™ after Job satisfaction, â€˜i1â€™ after Constant, c, câ€™ etc. However, in the Legend, only c and câ€™ were explained. Please explained every code written in Table 3.\r\n12)	Discussion: please add â€˜teachersâ€™ in the first sentence of the first paragraph \r\n13)	Practical implications: The examples of HR initiatives to increase job satisfaction have no scientific support cited. Please cite relevant literature.\r\n14)	My suggestion is to add a Conclusion section at the end of the manuscript.\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/', '2018-07-11 08:42:51', NULL, 1),
(35, 2, 256, 32, 32, 52, '[PRoUSt] Editor Decision', 'Martina Dwi Mustika:\r\n\r\nWe have reached a decision regarding your submission to Psychological Research on Urban Society, "How a Leader Transforms Employeesâ€™ Psychological Empowerment Into Innovative Work Behavior".\r\n\r\nOur decision is: Resubmit\r\n\r\nDebora Eflina Purba\r\nUniversitas Indonesia\r\neflina@gmail.com\r\n\r\nReviewer''s comment: \r\nThe paper is written well and fairly straightforward. My biggest concern is that it does not articulate its contribution to the literature given existing literature on these variables already exist.  The contribution of the paper needs to be better articulated. However, the very simply hypothesis. Perhaps a different analysis with additional variables may make the paper more interesting.\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/', '2018-08-13 13:01:22', NULL, 1),
