(16, 'en_US', 'title', 'A Two-Dimensional Framework for Analyzing Facebook Use and Subjective Well-Being', 'string'),
(16, 'en_US', 'cleanTitle', 'A TwoDimensional Framework for Analyzing Facebook Use and Subjective WellBeing', 'string'),
(16, 'en_US', 'abstract', '<p>The present research aimed to organize the array of Facebook activities by proposing a framework that comprises two dimensions: mode of Facebook communication and motive of Facebook use.Â  Our research also aimed to address the less explored issue of usersâ€™ appraisals in addition to their Facebook use.Â  A new measure, the Facebook Use and Satisfaction Scale, was constructed. Among 155 undergraduates (43% men, mean age = 21.02 years), the results indicated that satisfaction with both private and public social communication was positively linked with positive affect but not negative affect.Â  More importantly, satisfaction with private social communication explained 9% of the variance in positive affect beyond that explained by perceived peer support.Â  These results point to the utility of the proposed two-dimensional framework in the study of Facebook satisfaction.</p>', 'string'),
