he data collection process was conducted during school hours using paper and pencil questionnaires. Present study found that adolescents in Jakarta have numerous mental health problems. This study indicated that the prevalence of mental health problem among adolescents in urban Jakarta is high. Our study suggested that comprehensive mental health intervention in urgently needed to help these youths in optimizing their development.\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.psikologi.ui.ac.id/index.php/journal'),
