(215, 257, 28, 49, '2018-09-17 13:02:40', '202.51.119.91', NULL, '"Dewi Kumalasari" <dewi.kumalasari@yarsi.ac.id>', '"Dewi Maulina" <dewi.maulina140105@gmail.com>', NULL, NULL, 'The Effectiveness of Behavioral Skills Training (BST) Program to Improve Personal Safety Skills for Down syndrome Adolescent with Mild Intellectual Disability', 'Assalamu''alaykum wrb\r\n\r\nSelamat siang Ibu Dewi Maulina,\r\n\r\nSaya sudah mengunduh hasil review artikel saya dari web ini, namun dalam hasil review tersebut saya tidak menemukan bagian-bagian yang ditandai untuk diperbaiki. Mohon kiranya saya diinformasikan bagian mana dari artikel saya yang perlu diperbaiki. Terimakasih\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/'),
(216, 257, 28, 8, '2018-09-19 11:45:36', '10.5.152.101', NULL, '"Dewi Maulina" <dewi.maulina140105@gmail.com>', '"Dewi Kumalasari" <dewi.kumalasari@yarsi.ac.id>', 'fafadana@gmail.com', 'dewi.maulina140105@gmail.com', '[PRoUSt] Editor Decision', 'Dear Dewi Kumalasari,\r\n\r\nThank you for considering the Psychological Research on Urban Society as an outlet for your work.  I have received an expert review of your manuscript entitled "The Effectiveness of Behavioral Skills Training (BST) Program to Improve Personal Safety Skills for Down syndrome Adolescent with Mild Intellectual Disability", and I have also read the\r\nmanuscript independently of the reviewerâ€™s comments. Both the reviewer and I agree that the topic is important and is in line with our journalâ€™s theme. However, we also are in agreement that the manuscript still needs to be revised to meet the standard of scientific article.\r\nBelow I include the excellent and detailed comments from our reviewer for your consideration to improve the manuscript.\r\n\r\nTo submit a revision, please login with your account\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id with your username and password. If you have any problem regarding this step, please email us at proust@ui.ac.id.\r\n\r\nI would like to receive the revision within 7 days from the receipt of this letter. Please let me know if you would like to have additional time to revise the paper.\r\n\r\nSincerely, \r\n\r\nDewi Maulina\r\nUniversitas Indonesia\r\ndewi.maulina140105@gmail.com\r\n\r\nDr. Dewi Maulina, M.Psi\r\n------------------------------------------------------\r\nReviewer A:\r\n\r\nThere are some important details that were not included in the article, e.g., example of measurement items, duration of each session, why only 3 days, why two materials were covered in one session (did the author consider the fact that children with ID need more time to learn?), what kind of questions/measurements given to assess mastery of skill in the beginning of each session, what was the indicator that the subject had mastered the skill taught in previous session. Also, it was not clear if the three sessions were conducted in three consecutive days.  \r\n\r\nThe author made a strong conclusion that the program was effective to improve the subject''s safety skills; however, there was no follow up while the author already stated that repetition is required and encouraged parents to get involved in continuing the program. Therefore, I believe that follow ups are needed to ensure that the skills are not lost and maintained for longer period of time. Several follow ups in a span of at least 6 months are needed to observe the behaviour/skill acquirement and maintenance, Follow ups can also further support the study''s findings and conclusion that the intervention program was indeed effective for that subject to develop safety skills.\r\n\r\nReviewer B:\r\n\r\nIn Introduction, the author could explain more about urban context. For example, why it''s more dangerous to live in urban than in another context with limitation knowledge about sexual harrasment. Explanation about the process of BST program as behavior modification technique is needed.\n________________________________________________________________________\r\nPsychological Research on Urban Society (PRoUSt)\r\nhttp://proust.ui.ac.id/'),
