(26, 25, 'string', 'The use of words denoting countries can be more precise. For example, in the sentence " Fortunately, lessons have already been learnt by countries in North America and Europe, and those lessons might inform China about what are the best to protect innocent people from being criminalized by false memories." It is unclear about which institution in a country is the author talking. Is the author talking about legal institution in China? If so, which one? I am sure that the author is not talking about constitutional court. Please be more specific.\r\n\r\nIn addition, it would benefit the reader if there is a paragraph about the legal system or legal practice in China in the beginning of the paper. A discussion on the role of eyewitness in court(s?) will also be very helpful to the reader. At the present stage, it is unclear how false information from eyewitness can impact court (which court?) decision making in China.'),
