(26, 24, 'string', 'In the current paper, the authors have examined sexual compliance in a region in Indonesia and also asked for the reasons for this sexual compliance. They found that about a third of the respondents indicated to have experienced sexual compliance. \r\n\r\nThis is a very nice paper, well conducted and overall well written. Please find below some comments that might improve this paper even more. \r\n\r\nFirst of all, since this study is on sexual compliance, I would explain this term earlier in the paper. That makes it clearer to readers. \r\n\r\nConcerning the data analysis, I would suggest the following:\r\n1. If you give percentages, always add the n''s as well\r\n2. Give always exact p-values in the text and not p < .05. Giving exact p-values is much more informative \r\n3. Furthermore, to increase informativeness, add effect sizes (Cramer''s V) for example\r\n4. It is said that correlations were tested, but chi-square analyses examine relations, not correlations. I would change this\r\n5. Also, if you report means, add SDs as well. \r\n\r\nThe final comment is that this study needs a good proofreading. There are still quite some grammatical errors in the paper (e.g., p.9. ''women who lives'' should be ''women who live'').\r\n\r\nI sign my reviews \r\n- Henry Otgaar'),
