(26, 33, 'string', 'This paper contains an explanation of the approaches and methods that are new to psychology. The topic raised is not common to psychology in general. In some parts, the writing is very dense with a reference that is also quite new, in a sense not yet widely known by the community of psychology in general.\r\n\r\nThere needs to be an explanation that makes it easier for audiences from diverse backgrounds to understand what this article is saying.\r\n\r\nIn the introduction it is necessary to sit down the issues that will be discussed more clearly. It may also need an explanation of critical psychology and liberation psychology so that the audience can follow the course of reasoning in this article.\r\n\r\nConsider the communicative aspects of this paper as mentioned in the description on the Proust web site: "Authors of theoretical or highly empirical papers are encouraged to communicate the practical implications of their studies, and authors of practice-oriented papers should clearly elaborate the theoretical approach they are using." \r\n\r\nAdjustment style is important to do considering the substance of this paper is important to be known by the psychology community, including practitioners.'),
